Building AOSP JB on OS X 10.7 with XCode 4 takes just a little tweak to your build. Instead of running just make you need to run;
make CC=&ldquo;gcc&rdquo; CXX=&ldquo;g++&rdquo;
Which will allow the build to complete.

If you enable USB debug mode on the Q, then use adb shell you can start the settings app using the command;
am start -a android.intent.action.MAIN -n com.android.settings/.Settings
Once you have done this you can &ldquo;configure&rdquo; it using;
input keyevent xxxx
where xxxx is one of the key events from http://developer.android.com/reference/android/view/KeyEvent.html (e.g. input keyevent 20 is the same as pressing down on the dpad).
It&rsquo;s a bit time consuming, but it should be enough to get the Q working with a mouse ;)

